Package: statguide
Type: Package
Title: Simple Guide to Basic Statistical Tests
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person(
      "Ada", "Vestli",
      email = "adves1313@uib.no",
      role = c("aut", "cre")
    )
  )
Description: This package provides a simple guidance tool for selecting appropriate
    basic statistical tests based on the structure of a dataset. It is designed to
    support learning and decision-making, not to replace statistical judgement. The
    package handles a limited set of introductory-level scenarios and requires the
    user to explicitly specify the outcome and predictor variables when needed,
    ensuring that no incorrect assumptions are made about variable roles. Supported
    analyses include group comparison tests for numeric outcomes with categorical
    predictors, chi-square or Fisher tests for categorical associations, correlation
    for symmetric numeric–numeric relationships, and simple linear regression when
    the user defines the direction of the relationship. More advanced methods such
    as ordinal regression, multinomial regression, logistic regression with
    continuous predictors, mixed-effects models, repeated-measures designs, survival
    analysis, and multivariate techniques are intentionally outside the scope of the
    package. The aim is to offer clear, structured guidance for common and
    unambiguous statistical situations.
